FOX RIVER PAPER CO. v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 5241. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. May 14, 1934. A. E. James, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Robert H. Jackson and W. Frank Gibbs, both of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before ALSCHULER, EVANS, and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for petitioner, it is ordered and adjudged that this cause he docketed in this court, and that the petition for a review of the decision of the United States Board of Tax Appeals, entered in this cause on October 18,1933, be, and the,same is hereby, dismissed.
